[normal]WHAT [bold]GOVERNMENT HAS[bold] ANNOUNCED[bold]&#xa0;[bold]“The Government will secure the universal postal service for the benefit of all users by securing Royal Mail’s future through the introduction of private sector capital and associate disciplines. 
[normal]This will be achieved through:
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]delivering a sale of shares in Royal Mail within this Parliament;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]creating an employee share scheme that, as Parliament has decided, will lead to at least 10% of the company in employee ownership, to drive stronger staff engagement; and
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]delivering a financial outcome for the taxpayer, which when considered in the context of the overarching policy objective, represents overall value for money.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The institutional offer and the retail offer opened on 27 September 
[normal]and are 
[normal]expected to close on 8 October 2013. Conditional dealings are expected to commence on 11 October and Admission to the London Stock Exchange is expected to take place on 15 October.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]HMG intends to dispose of a majority stake including, leaving HMG with a residual holding between 30%. and 49.9%. 
[normal]The
[normal] 
[normal]Base 
[normal]Offer 
[normal]size will be 
[normal]between 40.1 per cent. and 52.2 per cent. of Royal Mail’s share capital
[normal], with additional s
[normal]hares representing up to 15 per cent. of the Base Offer also being made available 
[normal]through
[normal] 
[normal]o
[normal]ver
[normal]-allotment Arrangements.
[normal] 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In addition
[normal],
[normal] 10 per cent of Royal Mail shares will be made available for free to around 150,000 eligible UK-based Royal Mail employees under the Employee Share Scheme. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The e
[normal]xpected
[normal] Offer price range 
[normal]is 
[normal]260p to 330p per Share, implying a market capitalisation on Admission of between £2,600 million and £3,300 million.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]HM Government currently envisages that around 70 per cent. of the Base Offer will be allocated to institutional investors.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]IPO
[normal] includes a Retail offer
[normal], enabling 
[normal]members of the public
[normal] located in the 
[normal]UK
[normal] to apply for shares through intermediaries or 
[normal]direct to Government
[normal]. The minimum application size for members of the public is £750. Eligible Royal Mail employees can apply through the 
[normal]Employee Priority Offer
[normal] which has a minimum application size of £500. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Royal Mail intends to propose a final dividend only, to be paid in July 2014, of £133 million. In subsequent financial years Royal Mail intends to pursue a progressive dividend policy having regard to the normalised earnings progression of the Group. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]SAFEGUARDS[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The Universal Postal Service[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]delivery of letters six days per week to every address in the 
[normal]UK
[normal] (parcels five days per week) at uniform and affordable prices; and 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]f
[normal]ree services for the blind.
